        <item>
            <key> <string>description</string> </key>
            <value> <string>Returns complete schema information for a specific portal type including all available columns and their properties.\n
\n
Results are returned in two formats:\n
1. \'content\' field: Human-readable formatted display showing all columns with their properties\n
2. \'structuredContent\' field: JSON object conforming to the outputSchema with the following structure:\n
   - portal_type: string - The portal type ID that this schema applies to\n
   - columns: object - Dictionary mapping column titles to their properties, where each property object includes:\n
     * default: boolean - Whether this column appears by default in listings\n
     * filterable: boolean - Whether this column can be used in search filters\n
\n
Use MCP_listPortalTypes first to discover available portal type IDs. The human-readable column titles are used as keys in the structured output, making it easy to reference columns in subsequent MCP_listPortalType calls. Non-filterable columns cannot be used in filter or sort parameters but may still be included in column_list for display.\n
\n
This tool is READ-ONLY and is NON-DESTRUCTIVE.</string> </value>
        </item>
        <item>
            <key> <string>id</string> </key>
            <value> <string>MCP_getPortalTypeSchema</string> </value>
        </item>
        <item>
            <key> <string>output_schema</string> </key>
            <value> <string>{\n
"$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",\n
"type": "object",\n
"description": "Schema information for a portal type, including all available columns and their properties",\n
"properties": {\n
"portal_type": {\n
"type": "string",\n
"description": "The portal type ID that this schema applies to"\n
},\n
"columns": {\n
"type": "object",\n
"description": "Dictionary mapping column titles to their properties",\n
"patternProperties": {\n
"^.*$": {\n
"type": "object",\n
"description": "Properties for a specific column",\n
"properties": {\n
"default": {\n
"type": "boolean",\n
"description": "Whether this column appears by default in listings"\n
},\n
"filterable": {\n
"type": "boolean",\n
"description": "Whether this column can be used for filtering and sorting"\n
}\n
},\n
"additionalProperties": {\n
"description": "Additional column properties (type, sortable, widget, etc.)"\n
}\n
}\n
},\n
"additionalProperties": false\n
}\n
},\n
"required": ["portal_type", "columns"],\n
"additionalProperties": false\n
}</string> </value>
